5000|$|Benzoin is {{also known}} <b>gum</b> <b>benzoin</b> or gum benjamin, but [...] "gum" [...] is {{misleading}} as benzoin is not a polysaccharide. Its name came via the Italian from the Arabic lubān jāwī (لبان جاوي, [...] "frankincense from Java"). Benzoin is also called storax, {{not to be confused}} with the balsam of the same name obtained from the Hamamelidaceae family.|$|E
